{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878026456,"sessionID":"ses_2856c05fdffe6ktlyOUUmKQdZd","part":{"id":"prt_d7a9434b7001oIVLGAUKlp0Mua","messageID":"msg_d7a942173001Us4GTxR5YmMyLG","sessionID":"ses_2856c05fdffe6ktlyOUUmKQdZd","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-aacd6942a1fa4860b39516c28ed8aad6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This design document outlines the architecture and implementation approach for the AgentRuntimeClient, a Python SDK client that provides a high-level interface for managing agents and their runtime sessions.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Components\n10: \n11: 1. **AgentRuntimeClient** - Main client class for API interactions\n12: 2. **Agent Management Layer** - Handles CRUD operations for agents\n13: 3. **Runtime Operations Layer** - Manages agent lifecycle and sessions\n14: 4. **Error Handling Layer** - Centralized exception handling\n15: 5. **HTTP Client** - Underlying HTTP communication (using httpx)\n16: 6. **Data Models** - Pydantic models for type-safe data handling\n17: \n18: ### Design Patterns\n19: \n20: - **Builder Pattern** - For agent configuration\n21: - **Repository Pattern** - For agent and session management\n22: - **Strategy Pattern** - For different runtime types\n23: - **Factory Pattern** - For creating agents and sessions\n24: \n25: ## Class Structure\n26: \n27: ### AgentRuntimeClient\n28: \n29: ```python\n30: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n31:     def __init__(self, base_url: str, api_key: Optional[str] = None, ...)\n32:     \n33:     # Agent Management\n34:     async def create_agent(self, config: AgentConfig, ...) -> Agent\n35:     async def get_agent(self, agent_id: str) -> Agent\n36:     async def list_agents(self, ...) -> List[Agent]\n37:     async def update_agent(self, agent_id: str, config: AgentConfig) -> Agent\n38:     async def delete_agent(self, agent_id: str) -> None\n39:     \n40:     # Runtime Operations\n41:     async def start_agent(self, agent_id: str, ...) -> RuntimeSession\n42:     async def stop_agent(self, session_id: str, ...) -> None\n43:     async def get_session_status(self, session_id: str) -> RuntimeSession\n44:     async def list_sessions(self, ...) -> List[RuntimeSession]\n45:     \n46:     # Private methods\n47:     async def _make_request(self, method: str, path: str, ...) -> Response\n48:     def _handle_error(self, response: Response) -> None\n49: ```\n50: \n51: ### Data Models\n52: \n53: All data models inherit from Pydantic's `BaseModel` for automatic validation and serialization.\n54: \n55: ## Error Handling Strategy\n56: \n57: 1. **HTTP Errors** - Map HTTP status codes to appropriate exceptions\n58: 2. **Validation Errors** - Use Pydantic's validation for input data\n59: 3. **Network Errors** - Implement retry logic with exponential backoff\n60: 4. **Custom Exceptions** - Create specific exception types for better error handling\n61: \n62: ## Async/Await Design\n63: \n64: - All public methods are async to avoid blocking\n65: - Use `httpx.AsyncClient` for non-blocking HTTP requests\n66: - Provide methods for both sync and async operations (future enhancement)\n67: \n68: ## Configuration Management\n69: \n70: ### Client Configuration\n71: \n72: ```python\n73: - base_url: str (required)\n74: - api_key: Optional[str]\n75: - timeout: int = 30\n76: - max_retries: int = 3\n77: - retry_delay: float = 1.0\n78: ```\n79: \n80: ### Agent Configuration\n81: \n82: ```python\n83: - runtime_config: RuntimeConfig\n84: - capabilities: List[str]\n85: - constraints: Optional[Dict[str, Any]]\n86: - resources: Optional[ResourceConfig]\n87: ```\n88: \n89: ## Testing Strategy\n90: \n91: ### Unit Tests\n92: \n93: - Test each method in isolation\n94: - Mock HTTP responses\n95: - Test error handling\n96: - Test data model validation\n97: \n98: ### Integration Tests\n99: \n100: - Test against real AgentRuntime service\n101: - Test end-to-end workflows\n102: - Test error scenarios\n103: \n104: ## Security Considerations\n105: \n106: 1. **API Key Management** - Secure storage of API keys\n107: 2. **TLS/SSL** - Enforce HTTPS for all communications\n108: 3. **Input Validation** - Strict validation of all inputs\n109: 4. **Rate Limiting** - Respect service rate limits\n110: 5. **Error Messages** - Avoid exposing sensitive information\n111: \n112: ## Performance Optimization\n113: \n114: 1. **Connection Pooling** - Reuse HTTP connections\n115: 2. **Caching** - Cache frequently accessed data (optional)\n116: 3. **Batch Operations** - Support batch operations where possible\n117: 4. **Timeouts** - Implement appropriate timeouts to prevent hanging\n118: \n119: ## Logging and Monitoring\n120: \n121: 1. **Structured Logging** - Use structured logging format\n122: 2. **Request/Response Logging** - Log API calls (with sensitive data redacted)\n123: 3. **Performance Metrics** - Track request latency and success rates\n124: 4. **Error Tracking** - Track and alert on errors\n125: \n126: ## Future Enhancements\n127: \n128: 1. **Sync API** - Provide synchronous versions of methods\n129: 2. **Streaming** - Support streaming responses for long-running operations\n130: 3. **Webhooks** - Support webhook notifications\n131: 4. **Event System** - Provide event-based API for agent lifecycle events\n132: 5. **Retry Strategies** - Configurable retry strategies\n133: 6. **Request Signing** - Support for request signing for enhanced security\n\n(End of file - total 133 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis design document outlines the architecture and implementation approach for the AgentRuntimeClient, a Python SDK client that provides a high-level interface for managing agents and their runtime sessions.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n1. **AgentRuntimeClient** - Main client class for API interactions\n2. **Agent Management Layer** - Handles CRUD operations for agents\n3. **Runtime Operations Layer** - Manages agent lifecycle and sessions\n4. **Error Handling Layer** - Centralized exception handling\n5. **HTTP Client** - Underlying HTTP communication (using httpx)\n6. **Data Models** - Pydantic models for type-safe data handling\n\n### Design Patterns\n\n- **Builder Pattern** - For agent configuration","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/design.md","time":{"start":1775878026445,"end":1775878026454}}}}
