{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878093557,"sessionID":"ses_2856c05fdffe6ktlyOUUmKQdZd","part":{"id":"prt_d7a953aba001eUtZgdvSw1GNh2","messageID":"msg_d7a9484530014yvdGj10pPWqOo","sessionID":"ses_2856c05fdffe6ktlyOUUmKQdZd","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-06a39e98f28e4230ac091f8f4b5ca8ab","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis design document outlines the architecture and implementation approach for the AgentRuntimeClient, a Python SDK client that provides a high-level interface for managing agents and their runtime sessions. The AgentRuntimeClient enables users to invoke agent workloads through the Router service with proper session management.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n1. **AgentRuntimeClient** - Main client class for agent runtime interactions\n2. **AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient** - Handles HTTP communication with the Router for agent invocations\n3. **Session Management Layer** - Manages session ID lifecycle (bootstrap/reuse)\n4. **HTTP Client Layer** - Connection pooling and request handling via requests.Session\n5. **Error Handling Layer** - Centralized exception handling\n6. **Logging Layer** - Structured logging for debugging\n\n### Design Patterns\n\n- **Context Manager Pattern** - For proper resource cleanup (`__enter__`/`__exit__`)\n- **Repository Pattern** - For agent runtime invocation operations\n- **Factory Pattern** - For creating HTTP sessions\n\n## Package Structure\n\nThe AgentRuntimeClient is part of the `agentcube-sdk` Python package:\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n| `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` (main public API) |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` (HTTP layer) |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes |\n| `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` (connection pooling) |\n| `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` |\n\n## Public API\n\n### AgentRuntimeClient\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n    ): ...\n\n    def __enter__(self): ...\n    def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n\n    def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n\n    def close(self) -> None: ...\n```\n\n**Instance fields:**\n- `agent_name: str` - Name of the agent to invoke\n- `namespace: str` - Kubernetes namespace for the agent\n- `timeout: int` - Default read timeout in seconds (default: 120)\n- `connect_timeout: float` - Connection timeout in seconds (default: 5.0)\n- `logger: logging.Logger` - Logger instance\n- `router_url: str` - Base URL for the Router service\n- `session_id: Optional[str]` - Agent runtime session ID\n- `dp_client: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` - Data plane client\n\n### Configuration\n\n| Component | Resolved settings |\n|-----------|-------------------|\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` |\n| `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Same timeout defaults; base URL constructed from router_url, namespace, agent_name |\n\n## HTTP Client Contract — Data Plane\n\n### Base URL Construction\n\n```text\nbase_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\nself.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n```\n\n### Endpoints\n\n| Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n|--------|-----|---------|------|\n| `GET` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` | — |\n| `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n\n### Session Bootstrap\n\nWhen `session_id` is not provided in `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__`:\n\n```python\n# GET the base invocation URL to bootstrap session ID from response header\nresponse = session.get(base_url)\nsession_id = response.headers.get(\"x-agentcube-session-id\")\nif not session_id:\n    raise ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")\n```\n\n### Timeout Behavior\n\n- **Connect timeout**: `connect_timeout` (default: 5.0 seconds)\n- **Read timeout**: `timeout` (default: 120 seconds) or per-call override\n- Timeout tuple: `(connect_timeout, timeout)` on each request\n\n## Session Lifecycle\n\n### Context Manager\n\n```python\nwith AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\") as client:\n    result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"hello\"})\n```\n\nOn context exit:\n- `close()` is called\n- Underlying `requests.Session` is closed\n\n### Session ID Management\n\n**Option 1: Bootstrap (default)**\n```python\nclient = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\")\n# Session ID is bootstrapped from Router on first use\nresult = client.invoke(payload)\n```\n\n**Option 2: Reuse existing session**\n```python\nclient = AgentRuntimeClient(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    session_id=\"existing-session-id\"\n)\n# Skip bootstrap, use provided session ID\nresult = client.invoke(payload)\n```\n\n**Error handling:**\n- If `session_id` is falsy when `invoke` is called → `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Exception Hierarchy\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n    def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n        self.exit_code = exit_code\n        self.stderr = stderr\n        self.command = command\n        super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n\nclass SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n    pass\n```\n\n### Error Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Exception |\n|----------|-----------|\n| Router URL not provided | `ValueError` |\n| Session ID header missing on bootstrap | `ValueError` |\n| Invoke called without session ID | `ValueError` |\n| Network errors | `requests.exceptions.*` |\n| Router returns 4xx/5xx | Handled by caller (SDK returns raw response) |\n\n## Dependencies\n\n```toml\ndependencies = [\n    \"requests\",\n    \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n    \"cryptography\",\n]\n\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\n```\n\n## HTTP Session Management\n\n### Connection Pooling\n\n```python\ndef create_session(\n    pool_connections: int = 10,\n    pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n) -> requests.Session:\n    \"\"\"Create a requests.Session with connection pooling.\"\"\"\n```\n\nMounts `HTTPAdapter` for both `http://` and `https://` schemes.\n\n### Default Parameters\n\n- `pool_connections: 10`\n- `pool_maxsize: 10`\n- `timeout: 120` (read)\n- `connect_timeout: 5.0`\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n- Test session ID bootstrap logic\n- Test invoke method with mocked HTTP responses\n- Test error handling (missing session ID, missing header)\n- Test timeout behavior\n- Test context manager cleanup\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n- Test against real Router service\n- Test end-to-end agent invocation workflow\n- Test session reuse scenarios\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Router Communication**: SDK does not set `Authorization` header on data plane (Router handles JWT)\n2. **Input Validation**: Basic validation of required parameters\n3. **Error Messages**: Avoid exposing sensitive information\n\n## Logging\n\nStructured logging via `get_logger`:\n- `INFO` level by default\n- Can be overridden via `verbose` parameter\n- Logs session ID bootstrap, invoke requests, and errors\n\n## Example Usage\n\n### Basic invocation with session bootstrap\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\nwith AgentRuntimeClient(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    namespace=\"default\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n) as client:\n    result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"What is the capital of France?\"})\n    print(result)\n```\n\n### Reuse existing session\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\nclient = AgentRuntimeClient(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    session_id=\"existing-session-id\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n)\n\ntry:\n    result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"Hello\"}, timeout=60.0)\nfinally:\n    client.close()\n```\n\n### Custom timeout\n\n```python\nwith AgentRuntimeClient(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    timeout=180,  # 3 minutes\n    connect_timeout=10.0\n) as client:\n    result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"Long-running task\"})\n```\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n1. **Async API**: Provide asynchronous versions of methods using `httpx.AsyncClient`\n2. **Retry Logic**: Configurable retry with exponential backoff for transient failures\n3. **Streaming**: Support streaming responses for long-running agent invocations\n4. **Metrics**: Track request latency and success rates\n5. **Event System**: Provide event-based API for agent lifecycle events","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/design.md","time":{"start":1775878093517,"end":1775878093554}}}}
